nodes.description:
When you're a professional voice talent and audio producer, you're job is to "act" through your voice. And, not only act, but also act like a real person. 

I get asked all the time by random people who know that I'm a voice talent to "talk in my voice-actor-voice." Well, I hate to tell ya, the voice that you're hearing IS my voice actor voice! I've discovered that people just want to hear a REAL person. So, whether I'm recording an eLearning course for social workers, a pharmaceutical sales demo, a new product feature narration for a flooring warehouse, or an internal corporate compliance training, I'm using my REAL voice.

My voice over work has been described as authentic, natural, intelligent, engaging, and clear. And (I got this the other day) warrior goddess. Ok, at 5'2", I'll entertain the idea of warrior goddess!

My clients agree that my work process is on-time, within budget, exactly what was needed, and just plain awesome.

I follow a couple principals as a business owner: take my clients seriously and take their needs seriously. All the rest just seems to fall in place.

Give me a call or a connect or shoot me an email! I'd love to meet you and see how I can help.

company.description:
This was my one and only "corporate job." And this was the job that sparked my career as an eLearning voice talent.

I never considered myself to be techy or computer savvy in the least. But a friend of mine convinced me to apply and I got hired. So I put 100% of my time and talent into learning and teaching computer applications to adults. I started off teaching adults how to use Word and Powerpoint. Then I moved on to HTML and then JavaScript and SQL. 

Before I knew it, New Horizons had me create a web based programming course. I got to travel all over the country teaching a week long course that I created. I got to teach people who wanted to further their careers by learning web based programming.

I also learned that teaching adults is different. Adults need to know why they are learning something and how to apply it. They also don't have to partake in educational courses--they typically want to partake in them. This fact meant that I had to offer stellar teaching--which I am proud to say I accomplished.

Then something even more amazing happened to me! I became a mom!
company.name: New Horizons Computer Learning Centers
